It is worth noting that regarding Hizbollah's role in the war ten years ago, the use of radiant energy weapons was mentioned. A more concise summation of the technology can be found in We Shall Prevail: Israel as Nothing But an APT (Achievements of Partisan Technology), which you will find under 'articles' at: http://www.manasjournal.org/cgi-bin/eparking/tpdav.cgi?user=Leafs9101 after stating the technology, the report states: "Especially striking is the huge quantity of radars that Israel had and how they subsequently stopped working one after the other. What that meant, is that the operation affected the control system of Hizbullah's anti-aircraft batteries in such a way that they automatically kept tracking shut radar powers, no matter how short the radar pulse was. As a result, the systems rendered themselves completely blind to friendly F16s, and immune to loitering heat seekers that are typically used by anti-aircraft batteries to hunt down offensive aircraft." The defeat of Israel the first time during the Six Day War suggests that Israel was then more advanced in technology, a fact corroborated by the precedent of the 2006 war, where it was not Israel's army that defeated Hizbollah, but a type of weapons manufactured in the laboratory that effectively demolished the Israeli war machine
